 claim to economic theory or practice, yet nonetheless dictate forms of economic activity. Contributing to economic anthropology, science and technology studies, energy studies, and the anthropology of expertise, this book is a map of the everyday infrastructures of economy and energy into which we are plugged as denizens of a technological world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEconomic anthropologyzUnited States. 0aElectric utilitiesxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aElectric utilitieszUnited States. 0aExpertisexEconomic aspectszUnited States. 0aMarketsxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aTechnologyxEconomic aspectszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aderegulation.  aeconomic anthropology.  aeconomics.  aelectric grid.  aelectricity.  aengineering.  ainfrastructure.  amarkets.  arestructuring.  athe United States.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073914540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362822940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503628229423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503628229/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DSLb2021